Describe a time when you and some other people made a plan to do an activity
- what it was
- when and where you made it
- what the activity was
- explain how you felt about the plan

I’d like to talk about a time when I made a plan with a group of friends, which was during my last summer break when we decided to organize a trip to Đà Nẵng. It was actually the first time we had planned a trip entirely on our own, so we were both excited and a little nervous.

We first came up with the idea during a casual meetup at a café near our university. From there, we started discussing the destination, budget, and timing. Since everyone had different schedules, it took quite a bit of effort to find dates that suited all of us, but eventually we managed to reach an agreement.

After that, we divided the tasks among ourselves. One friend took care of booking flights, another handled accommodation, and I was responsible for planning the itinerary. I tried to strike a balance between relaxation and exploration, so we planned activities like visiting Bà Nà Hills, spending time at Mỹ Khê beach, and trying local street food in the evenings.

I felt really excited throughout the whole process, but at the same time, I was a bit worried about whether everything would go according to plan. Fortunately, things turned out even better than we had expected.

What made the experience truly special for me was not just the trip itself, but the teamwork behind it. It brought us closer together and gave me a sense of accomplishment. Looking back, I feel really proud that we managed to plan everything successfully, and it’s definitely an experience I’d love to repeat in the future.
